articles.author: Donna Lu
articles.title: Dinosaur skull found in Queensland belonged to sauropod that roamed almost 100m years ago - The Guardian
articles.description: Fossil from fourth-ever discovered specimen of a titanosaur may reinforce theory that dinosaurs travelled between South America and Australia
articles.content:
A 95m-year-old dinosaur skull discovered in Winton, Queensland, has been identified by palaeontologists as the first nearly complete sauropod skull ever found in Australia.
